        <section id="hero">
            <div class="container">
                <h1>Your coding agent is an <span class="threat-text">attack surface.</span><br><span style="font-size:0.55em;opacity:0.75;letter-spacing:0.04em;">OpenGuard LLM Security Gateway</span></h1>
                <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:0.9rem;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0.08em;opacity:0.55;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 auto;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;">for AI Coding Agents</h2>
                <p><span class="threat-text">Prompt injections</span> hide in repos, docs, and pull requests — <em style="font-style:italic; opacity:0.6;">waiting for your agent to read them.</em> <span class="threat-text">Secrets leak</span> in every context window. <span style="color:#fff; text-shadow: 0 0 4px rgba(255,255,255,0.8), 0 0 8px rgba(255,255,255,0.5), 0 0 16px rgba(255,255,255,0.3);">OpenGuard</span> intercepts it all <span style="color:#fff">before it leaves your machine.</span></p>
